National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg to discuss transatlantic security issues, progress on commitments from the 2014 Wales Summit, and plans for the next NATO Summit in 2016. They reviewed the status of NATO's Readiness Action Plan, discussed the President's decision to maintain 10,000 U.S. troops in Afghanistan through the end of 2015, and discussed NATO's ongoing Resolute Support Mission. They also talked about the alliance's role in building the defense capacities of NATO partner nations and their commitment to defense investment targets agreed at Wales. Rice thanked Stoltenberg for his leadership and invited him to visit the U.S. in May.